@Schnappi: No, you can't.  
The "madness cards" he was talking about are cards with an ability (Madness) that allows you to play them for a special mana cost (most often being cheaper than the casting cost) at the time you discard them from your hand.  

Cards like the infamous [Psychatog](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Psychatog) are much better for such decks though, since 1. discarding the cards for it doesn't require any mana (after playing Urza's Guilt there shouldn't be much mana left unless you play it in the late game) and 2. the discarded cards are used for a more useful effect; to pump that creature.
